			vector-valued functions, partial derivatives, multiple
			integrals) as prerequisite (MA 215 / MA 311). CLAUDE.md frames
			MA 301 as the fuller vector-calculus course. Decide whether that
			foundational material should be added as an opening unit here.
		-->
	</subsection>

	<subsection label="ma301-resources">
		<title>Resources</title>

		<introduction>
			<p>
				The resources listed will be used in this course. You are expected to access and use them regularly, as each one plays a specific role in supporting your learning and success in MA 301.
			</p>
		</introduction>

		<subsubsection label="ma301-materials-textbook">
			<title>Textbook</title>
			<p>
				The online coursebook, below, will be your primary source for learning the course material. Reading assignments will be assigned regularly, and you are expected to complete them before class so you come prepared for discussion and problem solving.
				<dl>
					<li><title>Textbook</title><p>MA 301 Coursebook — an adaptation of <em>APEX Calculus</em> (CC BY-NC 4.0).</p></li>
